Apr 16 Session — Fixes That Landed

Tagged sim-verified (checked in simulator) or iPad-retest (touch/Pencil
dependent — Trevor verifies on Paige iPad before TestFlight cut).

(1) Text tool crash + white rectangle           [iPad-retest]
    CanvasStateManager passed UIKit-points screenSize where doc-space
    was expected; the renderer double-scaled the location ~1.72× and
    walked the blit destination off the texture → Metal-assert crash.
    Even when it didn't crash, blitEncoder.copy is a destructive byte
    copy with no alpha blend, so the rasterized text rect punched a
    hole through anything underneath → revealed the white canvas
    background as a "white rectangle".
    Fix: pass documentSize; rewrite renderText to rasterize text to a
    scale=1.0 UIImage, then route through the existing renderImage
    path which uses the proven premultiplied Porter-Duff blend.
    Text is now also undoable (before/after snapshots) and refreshes
    the layer thumbnail.
    Files: CanvasStateManager.swift, CanvasRenderer.swift

(2) Image import broken                         [iPad-retest]
    importImage called addLayer then immediately tried to render into
    layers[selectedLayerIndex].texture — but addLayer only appends the
    DrawingLayer; texture creation is lazy inside
    Coordinator.ensureLayerTextures, which only fires during a Metal
    draw cycle. Texture was nil at the moment of the import call → the
    guard returned early → image never landed.
    Fix: importImage now eagerly calls renderer.createLayerTexture()
    right after addLayer.
    Files: CanvasStateManager.swift

(3) Cut Rotate Left/Right toolbar buttons       [sim-verified]
    Redundant with two-finger pinch-rotate. Removed both ToolButton
    entries; viewfinder/recenter button stays.
    Files: DrawingCanvasView.swift

(4) Canvas zoom % moved out from behind gallery icon  [sim-verified]
    Old indicator was a top-trailing overlay that stacked behind the
    gallery button (50×50 pinned top-trailing). Moved to a persistent
    readout at the top of the floating toolbar; tap to reset all
    transforms. Rotation indicator stays at top-trailing — it's
